{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in water. Set aside.","Place chia seeds in mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to bowl with water then mix together well with a fork. Set aside to soak for 15 minutes.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease sides and line base of a cake tin (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper.","Place oil and maple syrup in mixing bowl then heat <b>2 min\/60°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add grated lemon zest and juice, reserved ground almonds, poppy seeds, salt, baking powder and bicarbonate of soda then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add cranberries and reserved chia mixture then mix <b>15 sec\/\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>15 sec\/\/speed 5<b>.","Transfer to prepared tin. Bake for 50-60 minutes (180°C), covering with foil for the last 15 minutes if browning too much, until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Leave to cool in tin before removing.","Once sponge is cool, use a bread knife to slice in half horizontally to create 2 even layers. Arrange a sponge on a cake stand then ice with vegan frosting (if using, see page XX) then top with other sponge layer.","Serve in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g water","3 Tbsp chia seeds","400 g blanched almonds","80 g rapeseed oil, plus extra for greasing","120 g maple syrup","1 ½ lemons, finely grated zest and juice (approx. 85 g)","2 Tbsp poppy seeds","½ tsp fine sea salt","½ tsp gluten free baking powder","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","100 g dried cranberries","1 batch vegan vanilla frosting"]}],"id":"r139720","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-bsdzuC1OGaI\/XZWqC3RsQNI\/AAAAAAAAfSU\/sG9XARh1HTQDxzPsYUzt4WEy-B8rY1U4gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_AjuSH2Ekmqo_ovPb.png","title":"Cranberry, Lemon and Almond Cake (egg, dairy and gluten free)","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.7 g","fat":"34.9 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"73.5 g","calories":"2705 kJ \/ 647 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, skewer, aluminium foil, serving plate or cake stand, bread knife, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Store in an airtight container - will keep for 2-3 days.","For a truly allergy free cake, always check that all your ingredients come from a source free of allergens."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","2h 25m","10 slices"]}